# ACID properties

- **Atomicity:** Wrap related writes in a single transaction; all succeed or all roll back.
- **Consistency:** Enforce invariants with DB constraints (FK, UNIQUE, CHECK), not app logic alone.
- **Isolation:** Choose isolation level deliberately — READ COMMITTED default; SERIALIZABLE for critical financial ops.
- **Durability:** Rely on WAL/replication; confirm fsync settings in production DB config.
- Keep transactions short — long transactions block other writers and increase deadlock risk.
- Avoid user-facing logic or external API calls inside DB transactions.
- Use savepoints for partial rollback within complex transactions.
- Handle deadlocks with retry logic and exponential backoff.
- Test rollback paths — partial failure bugs are common without integration tests.
- Document which operations require strict ACID vs eventual consistency.
